(13, '{\"bn\":\"Ó”╣Ó”£ Ó”ĢÓ”░Ó”Š Ó”ĢÓ”ŠÓ”░ Ó”ēÓ”¬Ó”░ Ó”½Ó”░Ó”£\"}', '{\"bn\":\"Ó”╣Ó”£ Ó”ćÓ”ĖÓ”▓Ó”ŠÓ”«Ó¦ćÓ”░ Ó”ÅÓ”ĢÓ”¤Ó”┐ Ó”ĖÓ¦ŹÓ”żÓ”«Ó¦ŹÓ”ŁÓźż Ó”åÓ”▓Ó¦ŹÓ”▓Ó”ŠÓ”╣ Ó”żÓ”ŠÓ”åÓ”▓Ó”Š Ó”ĖÓ”ŠÓ”«Ó”░Ó¦ŹÓ”źÓ¦ŹÓ”»Ó”¼Ó”ŠÓ”© Ó”¼Ó¦ŹÓ”»Ó”ĢÓ¦ŹÓ”żÓ”┐Ó””Ó¦ćÓ”░ Ó”ōÓ”¬Ó”░ Ó”╣Ó”£ Ó”½Ó”░Ó”£ Ó”ĢÓ”░Ó¦ćÓ”øÓ¦ćÓ”©Óźż Ó”¼Ó”░Ó¦ŹÓ”ŻÓ”┐Ó”ż Ó”åÓ”øÓ¦ć ŌĆśÓ”¬Ó¦ŹÓ”░Ó”żÓ¦ŹÓ”»Ó¦ćÓ”Ģ Ó”ĖÓ”ŠÓ”«Ó”░Ó¦ŹÓ”źÓ¦ŹÓ”»Ó”¼Ó”ŠÓ”© Ó”«Ó”ŠÓ”©Ó¦üÓ”ĘÓ¦ćÓ”░ Ó”ōÓ”¬Ó”░ Ó”åÓ”▓Ó¦ŹÓ”▓Ó”ŠÓ”╣Ó”░ Ó”£Ó”©Ó¦ŹÓ”» Ó”¼Ó”ŠÓ¦¤Ó”żÓ¦üÓ”▓Ó¦ŹÓ”▓Ó”ŠÓ”╣Ó”░ Ó”╣Ó”£ Ó”ĢÓ”░Ó”Š Ó”½Ó”░Ó”£ÓźżŌĆÖ (Ó”ĖÓ¦üÓ”░Ó”Š : Ó”åÓ”▓Ó¦ć Ó”ćÓ”«Ó”░Ó”ŠÓ”©, Ó”åÓ¦¤Ó”ŠÓ”ż : Ó¦»Ó¦Ł)\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p><br></p>\",\"bn\":null}', 'hj-kra-kar-upr-frj', NULL, '1726309045.png', 1, 1, 'published', 1, 1261, 1, 3, '2024-01-17 10:20:13', '2026-03-29 19:08:43'),
(14, '{\"bn\":null,\"en\":\"Most of all Muslims perform umrah In Ramadan beacause of it\'s significants\"}', '{\"bn\":null,\"en\":\"Umrah is the greatest Sunnah of our Holy Prophet (P.B.U.H). It is an activity for Muslims to perform anytime over the year. There is noobligation in times Muslim can do it many times and whenever he wants. Every muslim has a wish to perform UMRAH at least one time in their life. A well plan is required to go to his Holy place.\"}', '{\"bn\":null,\"en\":\"<h4>Most of all Muslims perform umrah In Ramadan beacause of it\'s significants<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Umrah is the greatest Sunnah of our Holy Prophet (P.B.U.H). It is an activity for Muslims to perform anytime over the year. There is noobligation in times Muslim can do it many times and whenever he wants. Every muslim has a wish to perform UMRAH at least one time in their life. A well plan is required to go to his Holy place.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h4>Ramadan is the best time to perform Umrah<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Ramadan is a blessing for Muslims from Allah. Most of the Muslims wants to perform Umrah in Ramadan. Muslims want to get the most blessings of Allah especially in the Holy month of Ramadan. The Prophet Muhammad (P.B.U.H) said: \\u201cPerform Umrah in the month of Ramadan, as its (reward) is equal having a hajj performed with me.\\u201d \\u2014 Bukhari..<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>On other side our Beloved Prophet Muhammad (P.B.U.H) said \\u201cPerform Hajj and Umrah continually, to remove poverty and sins just as the furnace remove impurities from metals.\\u201d That is why Muslims want to perform Umrah in the Holy Month of Ramadan. Many travel agents and different agencies offer different packages with hotel booking in Madinah and Makkah.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We would be delighted to provide you with an exceptional hajj experience this year.<\\/p>\"}', 'most-of-all-muslims-perform-umrah-in-ramadan-beacause-of-its-significants', NULL, '1726308985.png', 1, 1, 'published', 1, 1407, 1, 3, '2024-01-17 10:21:35', '2026-03-29 19:08:45'),
(15, '{\"bn\":null,\"en\":\"Rules of Ihram: Hajj and Umrah\"}', '{\"bn\":null,\"en\":\"Every religion has its own religious pilgrimage to be performed by believers. As Muslims, Hajj is mandatory, whereas Umrah is a voluntary duty. Hajj can be done only at a specific time of the year, whereas umrah can be performed at any time. The timing is what makes all the difference. But to perform both duties perfectly, you must follow the rules of Ihram Hajj and Umrah.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe implication of Hajj in Islam is undeniable. A Muslim who is financially independent and has the ability must perform Hajj at least once in his or her lifetime. The Hajj only takes place in the last month of a year according to the Islamic calendar. You can still perform this holy journey to Makka Sharif at any other time of the year, but it will be counted as \\u2018Umrah\\u2019, not Hajj.\"}', '{\"bn\":null,\"en\":\"<h4>What\'s Ihram?<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Hajj and Umrah both are incomplete without proper Ihram. This is the kingdom when you have to enter to affirm you\'re eligible as a pilgrim. This sacred state is taken into consideration to be one kind of cleansing rite to purify your inner soul. Whilst in Ihram, you have to observe some specific units of rules like proper attire, prayer, behavior, etc.<\\/p>  \\r\\n<p>You need to enter the Ihram country before crossing \\u2018Miqat\\u2019, the major boundary surrounding the place wherein Hajj and Umrah are executed. Ihram is relevant to all pilgrims regardless of their gender or age. It is a signal to show the team spirit of Muslims, and consequently all will be handled similarly in this holy pilgrimage regardless of who they\'re.<\\/p>  \\r\\n<p>Breaking a rule of ihram will suggest a kaffarah or penalty for the pilgrims. The penalties are already decided based totally on the diploma of rule-breaking. It is able to be fasting, feeding humans, giving sadaqah, and many others. The motive of such retribution is to make the pilgrims well privy to the non secular meaning of Hajj and Umrah.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h4>How to Enter Ihram?<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Before entering the Ihram state, you should know how to prepare yourself with proper measures. Ihram requires a specific style of clothing for both men and women. No scents should be applied as it will break your Ihram state. Even if such an event occurs,  you have to change the clothes to a new one.<\\/p> \\r\\n<p>Steps of entering the Ihram states are to be followed when you decide to perform Hajj or Umrah.  During the Ihram, some rules are different for men and women. However, before entering the Ihram state, you must follow some basic steps.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h4>For Women:<\\/h4><h4>\\r\\nCut off the nails and clean-up.<br>\\r\\nTaking a purifying bath.<br>\\r\\nWearing Ihram clothes.<br>\\r\\nPerforming the prayer.<br>\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/h4><h4>For Man:<\\/h4><h4>\\r\\nCutting the nails and beard.<br>\\r\\nShaping the mustache.<br>\\r\\nTaking a purifying bath.<br>\\r\\nWearing Ihram clothes.<br>\\r\\nPerforming the prayer.<br>\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/h4><h4>Rules of Ihram<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Men can\'t put on stitched garments, they have to wear unique Ihram dress. However, girls don\'t should observe such restrictions concerning clothes. They are able to placed on their ordinary clothes.<\\/p> \\r\\n<p>Male pilgrims can\'t wear footwear or socks covering their feet. This rule does not follow to females.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Guys can\'t cowl their heads. A girl should no longer cover their face or put on niqab and gloves.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>After coming into the Ihram, you can not reduce your hair or nails. Men can\'t shave their heads till the sacrificial animal reaches the area of sacrifice.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Male pilgrims have to deal with ladies in an appropriate way. Female pilgrims have to comply with a modest dressing fashion averting any make-up or perfumes.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>All pilgrims should refrain from all sorts of bodily intimacy.<\\/p> \\r\\n<p>Pilgrims ought to be careful with their conduct. They have to be humble and avoid the usage of any profanity in ihram.<\\/p> \\r\\n<p>You need to keep away from all forms of haram deeds.<\\/p> \\r\\n<p>After you\'ve got entered the Ihram state, you can not put on any perfume.<\\/p>\"}', 'rules-of-ihram-hajj-and-umrah', NULL, '1726308910.png', 1, 1, 'published', 1, 1490, 1, 3, '2024-01-17 10:23:03', '2026-03-29 17:45:29'),
(16, '{\"bn\":null,\"en\":\"When Does The Umrah Season Start?\"}', '{\"bn\":null,\"en\":\"For the people following the religion Islam, Umrah is one of the holiest event of their life. Every year millions of capable muslims assemble in Mecca & Medina with a view to enrich their bags of good deeds.\"}', '{\"bn\":null,\"en\":\"<h4>When Does The Umrah Season Start?<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>For the people following the religion Islam, Umrah is one of the holiest event of their life. Every year millions of capable muslims assemble in Mecca &amp; Medina with a view to enrich their bags of good deeds.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>So what\'s the unique fact about this event? Umrah can be performed any time of the year! This is one of the basic differences between Umrah &amp; Hajj. But still there are some particular times when it\'s the best for you to decide to go to those holy places and purify your soul for the sake of Allah.<\\/p> \\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Also there are some rules &amp; restrictions by the government of SA regarding Umrah. Let\'s find out clearly when does the Umrah seasons start-<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Traveling In Holiday Seasons<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Muslims around the world rush to perform Ramadan Umrah to get extra blessings or sawabs. As a result, pilgrims and other visitors alike get the holy cities jam-packed on that month. As Ramadan is a holy month a section of people prefer this month over others to perform hajj. Otherwise the same goes for the other holidays such as Christmas and Easter, where we can observe an increase in international visitors. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Affordable Staying Arrangements<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>It is clarified that most pilgrims can easily relate with the spike in accommodation prices in holiday seasons. As in the holidays they can get a reasonable break from their work, it\'s obvious to have more pilgrims performing Umrah on those breaks. But if you prefer doing Umrah in a cost efficient way, you can choose time except for holidays as the staying arrangements are much cheaper than seasonal times.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>Favorable Weather Condition<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>Every Middle Eastern country is known for their hot climate &amp; unbearable heat. From the English Calender\'s perspective we recommend you to avoid June &amp; July as they\'re the hottest month of Saudi Arabia. For the people with special health conditions, it\'s not a wise choice to perform Umrah in Summer. The cooler months in Saudi Arabia lasts from November to February. These months are preferable if you want to perform Umrah in a favorable weather.<\\/p>\"}', 'when-does-the-umrah-season-start', NULL, '1726308854.png', 1, 1, 'published', 1, 1536, 1, 3, '2024-01-17 10:24:34', '2026-03-29 20:38:48'),
(17, '{\"en\":\"What is Hajj Mabroor?\",\"bn\":null}', '{\"en\":\"Mabroor is an Arabic word that comes from the word \\u201cBirr\\u201d, which means appropriate behaviour\\/man or woman and pleasurable duties towards others. In Islam, Hajj Mabroor approach an widely wide-spread Hajj. A Hajj in which a person refrains from sins, worldly dreams and carry out all the rites and ritual just for the delight of almighty Allah and by way of doing that, he will gain full reward from Allah, which is not anything much less than Paradise, and that is an agreed-upon Hadith (Sahih al-Bukhari 1773). It means that the reward for an typical Hajj will encompass now not simply worldly blessings along with forgiveness of sins and redemption from Hell, however also Jannah (Paradise).\",\"bn\":null}', '{\"en\":\"<p>Mabroor is an Arabic word that comes from the word \\u201cBirr\\u201d, which means appropriate behaviour\\/man or woman and pleasurable duties towards others. In Islam, Hajj Mabroor approach an widely wide-spread Hajj. A Hajj in which a person refrains from sins, worldly dreams and carry out all the rites and ritual just for the delight of almighty Allah and by way of doing that, he will gain full reward from Allah, which is not anything much less than Paradise, and that is an agreed-upon Hadith (Sahih al-Bukhari 1773). It means that the reward for an typical Hajj will encompass now not simply worldly blessings along with forgiveness of sins and redemption from Hell, however also Jannah (Paradise).<\\/p><p><img src=\\\"https:\\/\\/as.ashshura.com\\/storage\\/media_images\\/4eZE24031313.png\\\" style=\\\"width: 100%;\\\"><\\/p><p>How to know Hajj is Mabroor (accepted) or not?<br><\\/p><p>Hajj purifies the soul and washes away preceding sins. It isn\'t always a license to continue committing sins within the destiny. The return of a person who\'s higher than before is a sign of Hajj Mabroor. Here are some symptoms to help you to recognize whether or not your Hajj is Hajj Mabroor (widely wide-spread) or no longer.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>One of the signs of Hajj Mabroor is if you give up all of the awful behavior and sense you\'re a better Muslim now than before you left for the Hajj.<\\/p><p>If you are honest for your intentions even after Hajj and do now not brag about your Hajj, this is a sign of Hajj Mabroor.<\\/p><p>If you feel a exchange on your worldly desires and bask in doing excellent deeds and not do anything that Allah Almighty dislikes, that is a sign of Hajj Mabroor.<\\/p><p>If you are type to others and do now not hurt people along with your acts or words, that is a signal of Hajj Mabroor.<\\/p><p>The subsequent are a few symptoms of an widely wide-spread (Mabroor) Hajj. On returning from the Hajj, the pilgrim ought to hold to do excellent deeds, pray 5 times a day, and follow the sunnah of Hazarat Muhammad (Peace and benefits of Allah be upon Him) to acquire Allah\\u2019s forgiveness and praise of Jannah (Paradise) as in keeping with a Hadith narrated with the aid of Abu Hurairah (may also Allah be thrilled with him), the Prophet Muhammad (peace and advantages of Allah be upon him) said, \\u201cThe Umrah to the next Umrah is an expiation of all sins one commits among them, and praise for an prevalent Haj (Hajj Mabroor) is nothing besides Paradise.\\u201d<\\/p><p>According to this hadith, the reward for Hajj is the promise of Paradise and the remission of all your sins so you are sin-loose as if you were born that day. Reputation of our prayers is some other terrific reward for Hajj Mabroor. If we are searching for Allah for forgiveness, He, the most Merciful, responds to our prayer.<\\/p><p>Apart from the eternal rewards stated above, acting Hajj provides us with worldly blessings. In addition, Hajj improves our economic well-being. We will conduct criminal enterprise even as performing Hajj. Individuals who need to buy and promote can achieve this after praying and acting the Hajj rituals.<\\/p>\",\"bn\":null}', 'what-is-hajj-m